2. IDENTIFIED OPEN FILES & FILE DESCRIPTORS
----------------------------------------------------------------------
Inspecting '/proc/[PID]/fd' and executing 'lsof -p', the following 
critical file descriptors (FD) and stream pointers were mapped:

* FD 0 (stdin)  -> /dev/null
* FD 1 (stdout) -> /dev/null (or systemd journal pointer)
* FD 2 (stderr) -> /var/log/nginx/error.log
* FD 4 (socket) -> listen network socket [anon_inode:bdev]
* FD 5 (file)   -> /var/log/nginx/access.log

Technical Observation: 
Nginx cleanly routes its standard error stream (FD 2) explicitly to 
the physical error.log file on disk, decoupling it from the standard 
terminal interface output.


